Pre-Game Insights: Estonia are on a run of four straight wins in the UEFA Nations League, scoring 10 goals and conceding twice since losing 2-0 against Cyprus in March 2022.
Slovakia have won just one of their last five Nations League games while losing three and picking up one draw since June 2022.
Estonia will host Slovakia in their first meeting since 2005, with Slovakia having a strong historical performance record against Estonia.
Miscellaneous Highlights: This will be the third-ever meeting between Estonia and Slovakia, with Slovakia having a 2-1 victory in Tallinn and a 1-0 win in the return fixture.
Estonia secured the 2024 Baltic Cup crown in June, defeating Lithuania on penalties.
